<p>at 4 miles turned off road in bush &amp; advanced quietly by the side of hedges, across fields, keeping in touch with rear of infantry.<br/>At about 10 our outposts got into touch with enemy (69th Batt) outposts who retired our main column, just as dinner was <strike>ready</strike> timed (Dinner. one piece bread &amp; salmon)<br/>Next we moved off &amp; negotiated a large hill &amp; a ridge, coming on massed infantry in a hollow.<br/>Here was General directing operations of infantry to attack main position of enemy on large hill topped</p>
